WEBVTT

00:08.809 --> 00:10.744
[***]

00:55.489 --> 00:56.590
[WHISTLE TWEETS]

01:02.663 --> 01:05.399
[HUMMING]

01:05.433 --> 01:07.135
Hm.

01:18.646 --> 01:20.514
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

01:32.626 --> 01:34.595
All right.

01:34.628 --> 01:36.464
We're out of tea bags.

01:36.497 --> 01:38.399
[HUMMING]

01:41.335 --> 01:43.137
Any delays?

01:43.171 --> 01:45.206
A slight snarl-up
in Basingstoke.

01:45.239 --> 01:47.141
[INHALES SHARPLY]

01:49.443 --> 01:50.778
Fuck Basingstoke.

01:50.811 --> 01:52.613
[BOTH LAUGH]

01:59.453 --> 02:02.156
ED:
This-- This i-is not
an airport.

02:02.190 --> 02:03.424
Th-th-that's the trouble.

02:03.457 --> 02:04.758
[SPEAKS
FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

02:04.792 --> 02:06.894
Yeah, yeah.
Well, we're in Woking.

02:06.927 --> 02:09.397
[STUTTERING]
Uh, I don't quite--

02:09.430 --> 02:11.865
Well, you've done it,
but we're in Woking.

02:16.970 --> 02:18.739
You guys should
really get a lift.

02:18.772 --> 02:21.275
Yeah, we really should.

02:21.309 --> 02:23.244
[PHONE RINGING]

02:23.277 --> 02:24.945
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

02:24.978 --> 02:26.580
Hi.

02:26.614 --> 02:29.283
No, of course
I can't come home.

02:29.317 --> 02:30.784
Of course I can't.

02:30.818 --> 02:32.786
Because I'm at work.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.755
[TOILET FLUSHING]

02:36.290 --> 02:37.958
Of course I do.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.728
No, of course I do.

02:40.761 --> 02:43.631
Please don't shout.

02:45.566 --> 02:46.700
[DOOR OPENS]

02:48.602 --> 02:49.803
Toilet's blocked.

02:49.837 --> 02:52.606
Yes, sir.
Yeah. It is.

02:56.877 --> 02:59.213
[GRUNTS]

02:59.247 --> 03:00.548
Five day return,
please.

03:00.581 --> 03:02.550
Yes, coming right up.

03:02.583 --> 03:05.253
Uh, where to?

03:05.286 --> 03:07.755
You look like you're having
a worse day than I am.

03:14.362 --> 03:16.897
Why are you looking at me
like that?

03:16.930 --> 03:18.466
Do you want one?

03:18.499 --> 03:19.833
Uh, no, thank you.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.702
Uh, I need the destination
of your ticket,

03:21.735 --> 03:25.306
and I'm afraid I need you to
extinguish that cigarette. Ha.

03:25.339 --> 03:27.708
Ha. Didn't I say?
That's why I need this.

03:27.741 --> 03:31.245
Calms my vastly
overheating brain.

03:31.279 --> 03:32.413
Macon Heights.

03:33.781 --> 03:35.516
Macon Heights?

03:35.549 --> 03:37.485
That's right.
Macon Heights.

03:37.518 --> 03:39.420
Um, ha.

03:39.453 --> 03:41.455
There's no such station.

03:41.489 --> 03:43.023
Check the computer.

03:43.056 --> 03:44.525
A ticket to
Macon Heights.

03:44.558 --> 03:46.727
I've worked here over
20 years, madam.

03:46.760 --> 03:50.464
M-A-C-O-N Heights.

03:50.498 --> 03:53.834
Uh, what train were
you considering getting?

03:53.867 --> 03:56.270
Uh, do you know the time?

03:56.304 --> 03:58.872
5:19. I can also take
the 1:19 or the 9:19.

03:58.906 --> 04:01.309
Well, there you go.
That's the Alton train.

04:01.342 --> 04:02.543
You see?

04:02.576 --> 04:04.712
Stops at Brookwood,
Ash Vale,

04:04.745 --> 04:07.715
Aldershot, Farnham, Bentley,
and then Alton.

04:07.748 --> 04:11.018
There's no Macon Heights,
I'm afraid. Heh.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.421
[TRAIN PASSES]

04:17.658 --> 04:19.593
[***]

04:45.619 --> 04:47.020
BOB:
Then she was gone?

04:47.054 --> 04:48.889
ED:
Yeah, some sort
of trick, I think.

04:48.922 --> 04:50.391
A sort of light thing.

04:50.424 --> 04:52.426
Okay.

04:52.460 --> 04:53.627
No. No,
it's okay.

04:53.661 --> 04:55.028
Still keeping
that up, are you?

04:55.062 --> 04:56.697
I dream of
passive smoking.

04:56.730 --> 04:57.865
[BOTH LAUGH]

04:59.967 --> 05:01.935
Macon Heights.

05:01.969 --> 05:05.773
Yeah. I keep feeling I've heard
the name before somewhere.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.375
Ed, Listen.

05:07.408 --> 05:08.576
I know I don't
have kids,

05:08.609 --> 05:12.846
but I mean to ask,
you're okay?

05:12.880 --> 05:14.014
Never better.

05:15.649 --> 05:17.385
See you tomorrow.

05:19.119 --> 05:21.054
[MUFFLED RAP MUSIC
PLAYING INDISTINCTLY]

05:34.902 --> 05:38.539
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER POLICE RADIO]

05:45.813 --> 05:47.381
Shit. They called
the police?

05:47.415 --> 05:49.116
MARY:
She did. I phoned you.

05:49.149 --> 05:52.453
I didn't think
she'd call the police.

05:58.592 --> 06:00.428
OFFICER:
She'll not be
pressing charges.

06:00.461 --> 06:01.629
ED:
Oh, good.

06:01.662 --> 06:02.896
Th-that's good.

06:02.930 --> 06:04.932
But she
is very upset.

06:04.965 --> 06:06.600
A 15-year-old girl,
you understand?

06:06.634 --> 06:09.437
Well, we're very sorry.

06:09.470 --> 06:11.605
Aren't we, Sam?
She laughed at me.

06:11.639 --> 06:13.073
There is gonna
come a point--

06:13.106 --> 06:14.475
No, there won't. No.

06:14.508 --> 06:15.843
We won't let it.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.778
OFFICER:
--where we can't
excuse him.

06:21.081 --> 06:23.083
I just got angry.

06:24.785 --> 06:26.554
ED:
And I understand
that it's just--

06:26.587 --> 06:29.823
I shouldn't scare people.

06:29.857 --> 06:31.091
I shouldn't
scare people.

06:31.124 --> 06:32.860
Sam, I'm trying
to talk to you here.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.695
SAM:
I shouldn't scare
people, but I do.

06:35.929 --> 06:38.499
But I do,
I do scare people.

06:38.532 --> 06:40.468
[JAZZ SONG PLAYING
ON RECORD PLAYER]

06:43.170 --> 06:46.440
Hang on, have you
been raiding my, um--

06:48.241 --> 06:50.578
Oh.

06:50.611 --> 06:53.046
Pray silence
for Louie Bellson.

06:54.882 --> 06:56.884
You used to listen to this
when you were little.

06:56.917 --> 06:59.186
Count how many notes he plays
in the next five seconds.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.589
L-listen to that sax.
Go on. Go on, then.

07:01.622 --> 07:04.091
Phew-phew-phew.
Go on, count. Go on.

07:04.124 --> 07:06.960
Go on, count them.
Come on. Count them.

07:06.994 --> 07:08.562
You can't, though,

07:08.596 --> 07:10.498
because it's physically
impossible, it is.

07:10.531 --> 07:12.132
Too many notes to count.

07:12.165 --> 07:14.101
[LAUGHS]

07:18.639 --> 07:21.208
This, um--
Did she say anything

07:21.241 --> 07:23.243
or-or do anything
to provoke you?

07:23.276 --> 07:24.645
I've forgotten, so...

07:24.678 --> 07:27.515
[RECORD SCRATCHES,
MUSIC STOPS]

07:27.548 --> 07:28.982
Well...

07:37.991 --> 07:39.793
Okay, kiddo.

07:40.994 --> 07:42.696
Okey-doke.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.705
[TRAIN PASSING]

07:57.711 --> 07:59.212
Come in.

08:00.681 --> 08:04.718
Please sit down, madam.
Please sit down.

08:04.752 --> 08:06.053
Please sit.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.155
I just want
to buy a ticket.

08:08.188 --> 08:10.724
Why do I feel like I'm being
interviewed by Special Branch?

08:10.758 --> 08:13.026
Ed says you take
the Alton train.

08:13.060 --> 08:14.227
That's correct.

08:14.261 --> 08:16.163
The 9:19 train to Alton.

08:16.196 --> 08:20.033
The 9:19, or the 13:19,
or the 17:19.

08:20.067 --> 08:22.536
But mostly the 9:19.

08:22.570 --> 08:25.639
How long is the trip?
How long does it take?

08:25.673 --> 08:28.175
Twenty-eight minutes,
precisely.

08:28.208 --> 08:29.777
It's supposed to,

08:29.810 --> 08:31.679
though it's recently
become less reliable.

08:31.712 --> 08:33.647
BOB:
What sort of place
is Macon Heights?

08:33.681 --> 08:36.283
How many live there?

08:36.316 --> 08:38.552
Five thousand.
I don't know.

08:38.586 --> 08:40.554
And does it have
a large employer?

08:40.588 --> 08:43.557
A brewery? A power station?
A call center?

08:43.591 --> 08:46.093
No. Nothing big like that.

08:46.126 --> 08:48.929
I work accounts
at Bradshaw Insurance.

08:50.230 --> 08:51.799
What's the problem?

08:54.034 --> 08:56.169
This is a map
of our local network.

08:56.203 --> 09:00.674
I'll show you in particular
Farnham, and then Bentley.

09:00.708 --> 09:03.611
Do you notice there
are no stops in between?

09:03.644 --> 09:04.778
[TRAIN PASSES, THEN SILENCE]

09:10.784 --> 09:12.853
[SIGHS]

09:12.886 --> 09:15.322
Okay, how the fuck
did she do that?

09:15.355 --> 09:19.259
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
The train now standing at
Platform 6

09:19.292 --> 09:23.163
is the 9:17 serving

09:23.196 --> 09:27.234
Billingham, Farnham,
Bentley, and Alton.

09:27.267 --> 09:29.202
[***]

09:37.144 --> 09:38.278
MAN:
Are you on duty?

09:39.713 --> 09:43.083
Uh. No. No. No.

09:43.116 --> 09:44.384
Thanks.

09:44.417 --> 09:46.019
[DOORS BEEPING]

09:46.053 --> 09:47.287
[DOORS CLOSE]

09:49.022 --> 09:50.223
[WHISTLE TWEETS]

09:50.257 --> 09:51.892
[SAM SCREAMING]

09:51.925 --> 09:53.927
ED:
Sam, don't you hurt
your mother!

09:53.961 --> 09:55.796
That's enough!
Don't hurt him.

09:55.829 --> 09:59.132
Sam, please.
Please, please, please, Sam.

09:59.166 --> 10:04.137
DOCTOR:
When you lose control,
does it feel like anger?

10:04.171 --> 10:05.338
SAM:
No.

10:05.372 --> 10:08.375
Yes. It's, um--

10:08.408 --> 10:09.943
DOCTOR:
Does it feel different

10:09.977 --> 10:11.812
from what normal anger
feels like?

10:12.846 --> 10:14.247
Yes.

10:14.281 --> 10:16.249
DOCTOR:
And how does
it feel different?

10:16.283 --> 10:19.086
Does it feel sad?

10:20.954 --> 10:22.723
Yeah.

10:22.756 --> 10:25.726
DOCTOR:
Okay. That's interesting,
isn't it?

10:25.759 --> 10:26.894
SAM:
Is it?

10:30.263 --> 10:31.865
Dad.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.303
What? S-- Uh, sorry.

10:36.336 --> 10:38.438
Sorry. Sorry.

10:38.471 --> 10:41.241
Well, shall we leave it
there for now, yeah?

10:41.274 --> 10:42.442
Ed, Mary,
can I have a word?

10:42.475 --> 10:44.111
A-a word about what?

10:44.144 --> 10:46.046
DOCTOR:
Just some forms
I want them to sign.

10:46.079 --> 10:47.380
[SIGHS]

10:47.414 --> 10:49.249
Form a queue for the forms.

10:49.282 --> 10:50.884
Too many notes.

10:50.918 --> 10:52.052
[LAUGHS]

10:53.320 --> 10:54.755
Okay. Um.

10:54.788 --> 10:56.223
I'll just
wait outside

10:56.256 --> 10:58.926
with all the other
crazy kids.

11:01.361 --> 11:03.296
[***]

11:05.733 --> 11:08.869
I'm concerned about Sam.

11:08.902 --> 11:12.005
With the psychotic episodes
becoming more frequent,

11:12.039 --> 11:14.374
and the violence
getting worse,

11:14.407 --> 11:18.478
it seems likely that
his condition is deteriorating.

11:18.511 --> 11:21.982
We need to start talking
about how to prepare for this.

11:22.950 --> 11:24.885
[***]

11:33.093 --> 11:34.828
MARY:
Does he frighten you?

11:36.964 --> 11:39.733
Well, I'm frightened
for him.

11:39.767 --> 11:42.135
But does he
frighten you?

11:46.506 --> 11:48.742
Sometimes, yeah.

11:48.776 --> 11:50.010
Does he frighten you?

11:50.043 --> 11:52.445
He's my son.

11:52.479 --> 11:54.714
My son doesn't
frighten me.

11:58.251 --> 12:00.788
Do you remember, um--

12:00.821 --> 12:02.956
Do you remember
when-when we first met?

12:02.990 --> 12:04.858
Um, we were
introduced by, uh--

12:04.892 --> 12:06.359
Fuck, I f-forgot her name.

12:06.393 --> 12:08.128
On a train.

12:08.161 --> 12:10.230
She said, "This is Ed.
He works in trains,

12:10.263 --> 12:12.065
and this is Mary,
and she's on a train."

12:12.099 --> 12:13.333
Then she burst
into hysterics

12:13.366 --> 12:14.902
even though
it wasn't that funny.

12:14.935 --> 12:16.236
[LAUGHS]

12:16.269 --> 12:17.470
It took me almost
two months

12:17.504 --> 12:19.773
to convince you
out for a coffee.

12:20.941 --> 12:22.375
But I knew.

12:22.409 --> 12:24.912
I knew you
that were somebody

12:24.945 --> 12:27.014
I could build something
with and it--

12:27.047 --> 12:29.416
He reminds me
of you.

12:29.449 --> 12:31.184
That's why I can
talk to him.

12:32.820 --> 12:34.988
The true you.

12:35.022 --> 12:39.226
Not the one with the fake smile
spread across your face.

12:43.296 --> 12:44.898
Okay.

12:47.200 --> 12:48.969
And actually,

12:50.137 --> 12:51.404
I'm more frightened
of you

12:51.438 --> 12:52.973
when you've got
that fake smile on

12:53.006 --> 12:54.374
than I am of him.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.178
[SNIFFS]

12:58.211 --> 13:00.814
Okay. Good.

13:05.218 --> 13:07.154
[HUMMING]

13:13.927 --> 13:17.064
MAN [OVER PA]:
The train now approaching
Platform 6,

13:17.097 --> 13:21.534
the 9:19 train, boarding
at all stations to Alton.

13:21.568 --> 13:23.503
[***]

13:27.640 --> 13:30.043
[WHISTLE TWEETS]

13:31.411 --> 13:33.046
[DOORS BEEPING]

13:33.080 --> 13:35.015
[***]

13:44.591 --> 13:46.526
[CELL PHONE BUTTONS BEEPING]

14:03.376 --> 14:06.579
Uh, no, I'm not
collecting tickets.

14:11.351 --> 14:14.187
I'm just a passenger.

14:14.221 --> 14:17.257
MAN:
Yes, sir, we're
all passengers here.

14:24.998 --> 14:26.133
[***]

15:17.985 --> 15:19.252
ED:
Excuse me.

15:19.286 --> 15:20.520
Excuse me.

15:20.553 --> 15:22.389
You-- You can't--

15:24.024 --> 15:25.959
[PHONE ALARM BEEPING]

15:46.346 --> 15:48.281
[***]

16:35.195 --> 16:37.130
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

16:45.138 --> 16:48.041
GIRL:
Wait! Wait!

16:52.445 --> 16:54.147
Wait for me!

17:00.253 --> 17:02.189
[JAZZ SONG PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

17:06.326 --> 17:07.627
We do a table
service.

17:07.660 --> 17:10.230
Take a seat.
What can I get for you?

17:10.263 --> 17:11.431
Tea.

17:11.464 --> 17:13.066
WAITRESS:
How do you like it?

17:13.100 --> 17:14.501
Ahem, m-milk.

17:14.534 --> 17:15.735
One sugar.

17:15.768 --> 17:18.205
I'll bring it right over.

17:34.887 --> 17:37.190
White. One sugar.

17:37.224 --> 17:39.659
And a piece of some
apple cake I made.

17:39.692 --> 17:42.195
No charge. You look
like you could do with it.

17:42.229 --> 17:44.097
Right, uh, thanks.

17:44.131 --> 17:47.100
Uh. Very much. Yeah.

17:51.771 --> 17:53.140
I've never
seen someone look

17:53.173 --> 17:54.741
so frightened
by my cooking. Ha!

17:54.774 --> 17:56.243
Yeah.

18:03.216 --> 18:05.218
Well, actually,
it's, uh--

18:05.252 --> 18:06.553
It's divine.

18:06.586 --> 18:07.820
Divine?
Yeah.

18:07.854 --> 18:10.257
Ha-ha-ha.
I like divine.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.759
It's delicious.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.727
New in town?

18:14.761 --> 18:16.563
Yes.

18:16.596 --> 18:19.799
Well, not that I speak on behalf
of the town or anything,

18:19.832 --> 18:23.336
but I think you'll find a lot
of things divine around here.

18:23.370 --> 18:25.272
[SERVICE BELL DINGS]

18:39.319 --> 18:40.687
Oh, my.

18:43.223 --> 18:44.524
[CHUCKLES]

18:49.196 --> 18:51.164
[GIGGLING]

18:51.198 --> 18:53.266
Sorry,
we're just engaged.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.235
It's kind of--
It's glorious!

18:55.268 --> 18:58.305
Oh, well,
congratulations.

18:58.338 --> 19:00.740
MAN:
Thank you. Thank you.

19:00.773 --> 19:02.309
She said yes!
We're engaged!

19:02.342 --> 19:03.376
[ALL LAUGHING]

19:03.410 --> 19:05.378
[CHUCKLES]

19:05.412 --> 19:07.347
[***]

19:10.817 --> 19:11.751
MAN:
Hello.

19:25.298 --> 19:27.200
[BIKE BELL RINGS]

19:31.371 --> 19:33.340
[CHILDREN LAUGHING,
CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

19:43.483 --> 19:47.854
WOMAN:
Man sits alone
watching children play.

19:47.887 --> 19:50.357
In another world,
I'd be worried.

19:52.959 --> 19:55.395
He reminds me of my boy.

19:55.428 --> 19:56.763
WOMAN:
Which one?

19:56.796 --> 19:59.198
ED:
The one at the back there.

20:00.667 --> 20:02.935
Not very physical,
is he?

20:06.739 --> 20:08.441
Am I ill?

20:09.776 --> 20:12.745
Are you are a symptom
of my illness?

20:12.779 --> 20:14.947
You see, that's a classic
negative response

20:14.981 --> 20:17.384
from a classically
negative man.

20:17.417 --> 20:20.219
Why not see the possibilities
of the place?

20:21.821 --> 20:23.856
What is this place?

20:23.890 --> 20:26.326
Macon Heights.

20:26.359 --> 20:28.027
But Macon Heights is--

20:28.060 --> 20:30.997
It's not supposed
to be here.

20:31.030 --> 20:34.000
Did that apple cake
taste imaginary?

20:34.033 --> 20:36.336
Do those kids
look imaginary?

20:36.369 --> 20:37.870
It exists, Ed.

20:37.904 --> 20:40.773
You just don't want
to believe it can exist.

20:40.807 --> 20:42.775
Because it makes
you happy,

20:42.809 --> 20:45.412
and you're not used
to being happy.

20:47.480 --> 20:50.550
Maybe this is the world
as it should be.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.352
Cigarette?

20:52.385 --> 20:54.954
Maybe this is the world
that you need.

20:59.526 --> 21:03.029
Your train home leaves
at 20 past 7.

21:03.062 --> 21:06.499
Try to enjoy Macon Heights
until it does.

21:12.038 --> 21:13.973
[***]

21:39.466 --> 21:41.701
[GRUNTS]
Up we go!

22:06.926 --> 22:10.096
[TRAIN HONKS]

22:10.129 --> 22:12.064
[***]

22:34.053 --> 22:35.622
MARY:
Hiya.

22:35.655 --> 22:36.823
Hiya.

22:36.856 --> 22:38.057
MARY:
Good day?

22:38.090 --> 22:39.492
Strange day.

22:39.526 --> 22:41.728
Oh.

22:41.761 --> 22:43.863
Go put your feet up.

22:43.896 --> 22:45.732
I'm making a chicken pie
for dinner.

22:45.765 --> 22:46.933
Bit of a treat.

22:46.966 --> 22:48.468
Oh, yeah.

22:55.742 --> 22:57.677
[***]

23:26.539 --> 23:28.575
Remember when we
painted this room?

23:28.608 --> 23:29.842
[CHUCKLES]

23:29.876 --> 23:31.678
Always thought
we'd have a boy.

23:32.779 --> 23:35.448
Things happen,
I guess.

23:36.549 --> 23:38.117
Or they don't.

23:42.589 --> 23:44.791
I love you.

23:44.824 --> 23:45.758
[CHUCKLES]

23:47.727 --> 23:49.496
Still...

23:49.529 --> 23:52.799
I seem to remember
we had fun trying, though.

23:52.832 --> 23:54.867
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

23:57.269 --> 23:58.605
Mm.

24:00.707 --> 24:01.874
Mm.

24:01.908 --> 24:03.075
[BOTH GIGGLING]

24:03.109 --> 24:04.443
Oh!

24:13.753 --> 24:15.622
WOMAN:
Thank you.

24:15.655 --> 24:17.524
Thank you all.

24:17.557 --> 24:19.526
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

24:26.098 --> 24:27.800
[PA BEEPS]

24:27.834 --> 24:29.769
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

24:35.241 --> 24:37.009
[***]

24:59.966 --> 25:01.734
[PHONE RINGING]

25:01.768 --> 25:03.770
[ED SNIFFS]

25:03.803 --> 25:06.773
ED [STUTTERS]:
Yeah. I'm trying to locate
a reporter of yours.

25:06.806 --> 25:10.910
Uh, you don't seem to have
a-an e-mail contact.

25:10.943 --> 25:15.214
Uh, well, I wouldn't know.
Her name is Martine Jenkins.

25:17.016 --> 25:19.686
I need to know everything
I can about the place.

25:19.719 --> 25:20.953
MARTINE:
Why?

25:20.987 --> 25:22.989
Eh-- Um...

25:23.022 --> 25:24.757
It's, uh, for a project.

25:24.791 --> 25:26.092
[CHUCKLES]

25:26.125 --> 25:27.960
You do understand
I'm a journalist?

25:27.994 --> 25:30.563
We're a dying breed,
but we generally

25:30.597 --> 25:35.334
have an unerring sense of smell
where bullshit is concerned.

25:35.367 --> 25:36.936
[CHUCKLES]

25:36.969 --> 25:39.572
MARTINE:
How many times
have you been?

25:39.606 --> 25:40.873
Um... Ahem.

25:42.609 --> 25:44.343
Once.
Oh, I'm impressed.

25:44.376 --> 25:46.979
Normally people have been
eight or nine times

25:47.013 --> 25:48.247
before they look me up.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.082
I'm not the first, then.

25:59.926 --> 26:02.061
In my experience,

26:02.094 --> 26:05.031
the less I explain...

26:05.064 --> 26:06.966
the better this is.

26:08.935 --> 26:10.269
[MURMURS]

26:14.173 --> 26:15.742
[ED SCOFFS]

26:15.775 --> 26:18.177
This is still a town
that doesn't exist.

26:18.210 --> 26:22.181
It's a town
that almost existed.

26:22.214 --> 26:24.817
I think that's
somehow different.

26:26.218 --> 26:28.955
There was such a lot
to say about it.

26:28.988 --> 26:33.392
The pity was I just couldn't get
a big piece printed up anywhere.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.261
Well, who stopped you?

26:35.294 --> 26:37.229
Oh, no, no, there's
no conspiracy.

26:37.263 --> 26:39.231
They just didn't think
it was interesting.

26:39.265 --> 26:42.201
A dreamer dreams big.

26:42.234 --> 26:43.770
It blows up.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.772
He dies.

26:45.805 --> 26:47.006
He died?

26:47.039 --> 26:48.841
He won the bid,

26:48.875 --> 26:52.211
but there were
financial irregularities.

26:52.244 --> 26:54.313
Not corruption,
just incompetence.

26:57.349 --> 27:00.119
I've tried to visit,
you know.

27:00.152 --> 27:02.254
Of course I have.

27:02.288 --> 27:04.190
An ideal town...

27:04.223 --> 27:05.792
[INHALES SHARPLY]

27:05.825 --> 27:07.359
...that stays ideal...

27:09.161 --> 27:12.799
that can exist untouched
by reality.

27:16.202 --> 27:18.304
But the door
wouldn't open for me.

27:18.337 --> 27:21.140
Um... Who's this?

27:22.374 --> 27:23.876
That's his daughter,

27:23.910 --> 27:25.244
Linda.

27:25.277 --> 27:27.313
She found him in the woods.

27:27.346 --> 27:29.315
Overdosed.

27:29.348 --> 27:32.719
Two weeks after they took
the project away from him

27:32.752 --> 27:35.321
and gave it
to the next bidder.

27:35.354 --> 27:37.289
[***]

27:46.332 --> 27:48.000
You're just
saying nothing, are you?

27:48.034 --> 27:50.036
What?

27:50.069 --> 27:52.438
BOB:
You fuck off just before rush
hour, leave me on my johns.

27:52.471 --> 27:53.906
And you're just
saying nothing.

27:53.940 --> 27:56.375
Where'd you go?

27:56.408 --> 27:58.110
You doing something
you shouldn't?

27:58.144 --> 27:59.979
No.

28:00.012 --> 28:01.948
Once a family's broken...

28:01.981 --> 28:03.449
it doesn't get mended.

28:03.482 --> 28:05.885
Three kids by three
different mothers, remember?

28:05.918 --> 28:07.353
[CHUCKLES]
Three kids?

28:07.386 --> 28:10.990
Yes. I think I know
how many children I've got.

28:13.893 --> 28:15.327
I have to go.

28:15.361 --> 28:16.929
I'll take it
as annual leave.

28:16.963 --> 28:18.464
What?

28:18.497 --> 28:22.201
Ed! Ed, it's too late for me
to arrange cover.

28:22.234 --> 28:24.436
You can't just go.

28:24.470 --> 28:26.906
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

28:26.939 --> 28:29.075
Ed! Ed!

28:29.108 --> 28:31.510
Stop the train!

28:31.543 --> 28:33.112
Ed.

28:36.849 --> 28:38.785
[***]

28:41.988 --> 28:44.323
MAN:
Gets quite addictive,
doesn't it?

28:45.792 --> 28:47.827
Sorry?

28:47.860 --> 28:50.029
Watching the world go by.

29:08.280 --> 29:09.515
You came back.

29:09.548 --> 29:10.983
I did.

29:11.017 --> 29:12.451
I am so pleased.

29:12.484 --> 29:14.486
I made a ginger cake today that
you're gonna love.

29:14.520 --> 29:17.389
Then I will
have that and a...

29:17.423 --> 29:20.893
I was about to say
a cup of hot chocolate.

29:20.927 --> 29:23.529
Hot chocolate and ginger cake
is a tasty combination.

29:23.562 --> 29:25.131
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

29:25.164 --> 29:27.066
[JAZZ SONG PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

29:27.099 --> 29:29.035
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

29:36.976 --> 29:38.510
[SIGHS]

29:41.247 --> 29:43.315
[CHATTER, JAZZ MUSIC FADE AWAY]

29:43.349 --> 29:45.151
WAITRESS:
Feels better, doesn't it?

29:47.619 --> 29:49.188
Warning...

29:49.221 --> 29:51.323
this can get
quite addictive.

29:51.357 --> 29:52.892
[MOUTHS]

29:52.925 --> 29:55.227
My ginger cake. Ha.

29:55.261 --> 29:58.164
Oh, ha-ha-ha. Thank you.

29:58.197 --> 30:00.132
[INDISTINCT CHATTER,
JAZZ SONG RESUME]

30:10.009 --> 30:11.577
[BOTH LAUGHING]

30:11.610 --> 30:14.313
Sorry. We're just engaged.
It's kind of--

30:14.346 --> 30:15.447
It's glorious.

30:15.481 --> 30:16.448
[MAN LAUGHS]

30:16.482 --> 30:18.317
I-I-I don't understand.

30:18.350 --> 30:20.252
MAN:
Thank you. Thank you.

30:22.288 --> 30:23.856
[CHUCKLES]

30:26.292 --> 30:28.194
[ICE CREAM TRUCK
PLAYING MUSIC]

30:28.227 --> 30:30.196
[CHILDREN LAUGHING,
CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

30:38.104 --> 30:41.040
[***]

31:08.534 --> 31:11.470
[***]

31:19.645 --> 31:21.613
VOICE:
Dad.

31:35.527 --> 31:37.463
[MARY SOBBING]

31:45.304 --> 31:47.039
Mary.

31:51.177 --> 31:52.511
What's the matter?

31:54.213 --> 31:56.482
Just...

31:56.515 --> 31:58.350
thinking about
what could have been.

31:59.685 --> 32:02.721
What could have been
doesn't exist.

32:02.754 --> 32:06.925
[BREATHING SHAKILY]
There's only what is,
and that's you and me.

32:09.561 --> 32:11.397
And that's
good enough for me.

32:24.710 --> 32:27.646
[UPBEAT SONG PLAYING
ON SAXOPHONE]

32:47.566 --> 32:50.502
[SAXOPHONE MUSIC
DISTORTING, SLOWING]

32:55.741 --> 32:57.576
[RECORD SCRATCHES]

33:02.248 --> 33:04.716
[CLOCK TICKING]

33:07.519 --> 33:09.455
[***]

33:34.513 --> 33:36.215
[LATCH CLICKS
LADDER CLATTERS]

33:52.531 --> 33:55.467
[***]

34:30.202 --> 34:32.138
[***]

34:34.273 --> 34:35.841
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

34:42.214 --> 34:44.416
[BOTH SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

34:44.450 --> 34:46.385
[LAUGHS]

34:48.620 --> 34:51.457
[SONG PLAYING INDISTINCTLY
OVER STEREO]

34:54.293 --> 34:56.328
WOMAN:
Sammy!

35:17.449 --> 35:19.285
[CRYING]

35:37.236 --> 35:38.804
MARY:
Couldn't you sleep?

35:41.707 --> 35:43.675
What are you doing
with all these?

35:43.709 --> 35:45.311
What are all these?

35:48.314 --> 35:50.249
Do you remember
when we first met?

35:50.282 --> 35:52.351
On a train.

35:52.384 --> 35:53.852
Woman introduced us
and she said:

35:53.885 --> 35:55.654
"Here's Ed. He's in trains.

35:55.687 --> 35:57.489
[CHUCKLES]
And here's Mary.
She's on one."

35:57.523 --> 36:00.559
And what happened
after that?

36:00.592 --> 36:03.795
We fell in love, didn't we?
It's as simple as that.

36:03.829 --> 36:05.297
Ed?

36:05.331 --> 36:06.732
Are you okay?

36:08.534 --> 36:10.336
Ed?

36:10.369 --> 36:11.503
Where are you going?

36:12.438 --> 36:13.805
BOB:
Ed.

36:13.839 --> 36:15.741
Ed, there's been a problem
at Basingstoke.

36:15.774 --> 36:16.942
Fuck Basingstoke.

36:16.975 --> 36:18.744
Yeah, but it does
need sorting.

36:18.777 --> 36:20.246
Can we get some ETAs on it?

36:20.279 --> 36:21.613
I said fuck Basingstoke.

36:23.482 --> 36:25.251
MAN:
Ah, you're angry.

36:26.352 --> 36:27.619
Or upset.

36:28.787 --> 36:30.656
Or mad.

36:30.689 --> 36:32.691
Or sane?

36:32.724 --> 36:35.661
[TRAIN SIGNAL RINGING
IN BACKGROUND]

36:35.694 --> 36:37.296
What are you, Ed,
do you think?

36:42.334 --> 36:43.769
Excuse me.

36:43.802 --> 36:46.505
I'm looking for Linda.
Do you know who-- Linda?

36:46.538 --> 36:50.442
No, she wasn't called Linda.
She was called Jane.

36:50.476 --> 36:51.743
Lung cancer, you see.

36:51.777 --> 36:53.312
What?

36:53.345 --> 36:54.613
MAN: Lung cancer.
ED: This is important.

36:54.646 --> 36:56.815
I'm looking for Linda. Do--

36:56.848 --> 36:58.917
I'm sorry, you have me mixed up
with another man.

36:58.950 --> 37:01.587
"Go home," they said.
And then I found home.

37:01.620 --> 37:03.389
WOMAN:
They said you'd
be able to help.

37:03.422 --> 37:07.459
They said you were new.
And helpful. A new helpful man.

37:07.493 --> 37:09.361
They're gonna let him die,
aren't they?

37:09.395 --> 37:10.862
Why would they
let him die?

37:13.632 --> 37:16.568
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

37:29.815 --> 37:31.850
It's you. Thank God.

37:31.883 --> 37:33.552
Please help me.

37:33.585 --> 37:36.655
I'm looking for Linda.
A mistake has been made.

37:36.688 --> 37:39.358
Well, you're looking
in a bit of mess, aren't you?

37:39.391 --> 37:43.028
I'll fetch a cake
and one of your hot chocolates.

37:43.061 --> 37:44.996
[JAZZ SONG PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

37:53.339 --> 37:55.040
Please. Please help me.

37:55.073 --> 37:57.543
Do you know
where I can find Linda?

37:57.576 --> 37:58.777
No, love.

37:58.810 --> 37:59.978
I'm not sure I can

38:00.011 --> 38:01.580
find much at all, really.

38:01.613 --> 38:04.550
What is this place?
Macon Heights.

38:04.583 --> 38:06.852
But what's happened to it?

38:06.885 --> 38:08.520
You did.

38:08.554 --> 38:10.356
The truth did.

38:10.389 --> 38:13.692
[ANGRY TONE]
And we want it back
the way we had it.

38:13.725 --> 38:17.929
I just want to find Linda.
I just want to get my boy back.

38:25.003 --> 38:28.440
He told me he had a knife.
He told me I had to follow him.

38:28.474 --> 38:31.543
This older man took me
off of the path.

38:31.577 --> 38:32.911
I was 14.

38:32.944 --> 38:35.013
I was walking home,
just through the park,

38:35.046 --> 38:37.749
and there was a bit in the fence
that was broken.

38:37.783 --> 38:40.752
And he pulled me through,
pulled me by the rail tracks.

38:40.786 --> 38:43.822
He started to touch me.
He started to touch my breasts.

38:43.855 --> 38:45.824
No one had ever
touched me there before.

38:45.857 --> 38:47.759
I think I need
to tell you my story.

38:47.793 --> 38:50.128
No. No, I don't want
to hear your stories.

38:50.161 --> 38:51.697
I think that
part of you does.

38:51.730 --> 38:54.600
A part of you
has to understand it.

38:54.633 --> 38:56.768
Understand what
this place is.

38:57.769 --> 38:59.871
She took my son.

38:59.905 --> 39:02.608
I need to get him back.

39:02.641 --> 39:05.677
Was he in pain?

39:05.711 --> 39:08.013
She's very good with pain.

39:10.916 --> 39:13.452
When later, I fell in love,
and I tried to...

39:15.421 --> 39:17.856
It just didn't work,
and this--

39:17.889 --> 39:20.459
This is better.

39:20.492 --> 39:21.860
What was your son's name?

39:23.462 --> 39:24.696
[VOICE CRACKING]
Sam.

39:24.730 --> 39:26.932
S-S-Sammy.

39:28.133 --> 39:30.902
A nice name.

39:30.936 --> 39:34.640
[SOBBING]
I was frightened of him.

39:34.673 --> 39:36.742
No.

39:36.775 --> 39:37.909
No more of that. Not here.

39:48.687 --> 39:50.689
Coffee and walnut cake,

39:50.722 --> 39:53.725
made just the way
my mum used to make it.

40:00.499 --> 40:02.434
You'll remember
where to find her.

40:08.640 --> 40:10.976
[BOTH GIGGLING]

40:11.009 --> 40:13.979
Sorry, we're just engaged.
It's kind of--

40:14.012 --> 40:16.782
It's glorious.

40:16.815 --> 40:18.450
Stay out of my way!

40:19.918 --> 40:23.088
Thank you. Thank you.

40:23.121 --> 40:25.891
WOMAN: We're engaged.
MAN: Congratulations.

40:25.924 --> 40:28.193
WOMAN: Thank you. Thank you.
MAN: Fabulous. Fabulous.

40:30.095 --> 40:32.030
[***]

40:56.888 --> 40:59.591
A lot of people forget
I work at Bradshaw Insurance

40:59.625 --> 41:01.860
so kudos for that.

41:01.893 --> 41:05.196
I always tell them,
but they generally forget.

41:05.230 --> 41:06.598
How can I help?

41:06.632 --> 41:09.568
You've made a mistake.

41:09.601 --> 41:11.503
I'm not one of these people.

41:19.110 --> 41:23.014
And I need everything back
just the way it was before.

41:33.058 --> 41:35.994
[***]

41:36.027 --> 41:39.965
[KIDS LAUGHING,
CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

41:46.304 --> 41:48.239
[***]

41:55.847 --> 41:57.683
I take it they're not real.

41:59.317 --> 42:00.686
Aren't they?

42:00.719 --> 42:03.021
And nor are your
engaged couple,

42:03.054 --> 42:06.725
who have bashed into me
in the street three times now.

42:06.758 --> 42:09.728
Bit disingenuous...

42:09.761 --> 42:13.331
claiming your son reminded you
of the kid at the back.

42:13.364 --> 42:15.601
LINDA:
As I understand it,
he'd be at the front,

42:15.634 --> 42:17.969
probably ripping
the kite to pieces.

42:19.337 --> 42:20.906
Sit down, Ed.

42:28.346 --> 42:30.816
I want my son back.

42:30.849 --> 42:32.618
I'm not sure you do.

42:34.319 --> 42:38.690
People can't
just be extinguished.

42:38.724 --> 42:42.127
I have three rationalizations
I always give.

42:42.160 --> 42:44.796
First, is the damage
that's been done to yourself.

42:44.830 --> 42:46.698
Okay, enough with--
Second,

42:46.732 --> 42:48.700
is the damage
that's been done to others.

42:48.734 --> 42:51.770
And third,
perhaps most important...

42:51.803 --> 42:53.872
is the damage that's done
to him or her,

42:53.905 --> 42:55.340
the subject, if you like.

42:55.373 --> 42:56.875
Fuck you.

42:56.908 --> 42:58.076
Husbands wanting their wives

42:58.109 --> 42:59.678
to go through
that final round

42:59.711 --> 43:02.380
of painful chemotherapy.

43:02.413 --> 43:04.616
Children wanting their mums
to go on living,

43:04.650 --> 43:07.018
despite the pain.

43:07.052 --> 43:09.755
[SCOFFS]
What, so the answer
to life's problems

43:09.788 --> 43:12.758
is to stop living
in reality?

43:12.791 --> 43:14.726
Your son
was a shit son,

43:14.760 --> 43:17.896
and you were
a shit father to him.

43:17.929 --> 43:19.698
LINDA:
What's great
about that reality?

43:19.731 --> 43:21.332
ED:
You don't understand.

43:21.366 --> 43:23.869
There were moments of joy.

43:23.902 --> 43:27.973
There were moments
of incredible happiness,

43:28.006 --> 43:30.041
when Sam was happy.

43:30.075 --> 43:31.677
There was joy.

43:31.710 --> 43:34.179
Don't deny you dreamt
of another life.

43:34.212 --> 43:37.248
Dreaming is not the same
as wishing it's true.

43:46.024 --> 43:49.060
I want to see my son grow up
to be a man.

43:59.104 --> 44:00.305
I can tell you his story

44:00.338 --> 44:02.307
will just get
sadder and sadder.

44:02.340 --> 44:04.876
Then that should be
my story too.

44:07.879 --> 44:09.314
It'll break you.

44:10.481 --> 44:12.250
And it'll break your wife.

44:14.085 --> 44:16.688
He'll go to jail.

44:16.722 --> 44:19.157
He'll do terrible things.

44:19.190 --> 44:21.893
You'll do terrible things.

44:21.927 --> 44:23.461
You'll all be so unhappy.

44:23.494 --> 44:25.697
Then that is
how it shall be.

44:25.731 --> 44:27.699
Adopt. Foster.

44:27.733 --> 44:29.768
Find another child
that needs you.

44:29.801 --> 44:33.171
Engage in new possibilities,
a new life.

44:33.204 --> 44:34.472
You can rewrite everything.

44:34.505 --> 44:37.308
We had a child.

44:37.342 --> 44:38.877
I'd like him back.

44:38.910 --> 44:40.746
This is just guilt.

44:40.779 --> 44:42.047
No.

44:42.080 --> 44:45.150
This is love.

44:45.183 --> 44:47.385
He's what I made.

44:47.418 --> 44:50.922
We made. This is love.

44:53.058 --> 44:54.893
You almost sound convinced.

44:57.062 --> 44:58.329
I can force your hand.

44:58.363 --> 45:00.098
No, you can't.

45:00.131 --> 45:03.468
They all have to come and travel
through my station

45:03.501 --> 45:04.970
to get to Macon Heights.

45:05.003 --> 45:07.138
I'll tell them
what they're gonna lose.

45:07.172 --> 45:09.107
A life without truth.

45:09.140 --> 45:10.375
That won't stop all of them.

45:10.408 --> 45:12.377
It will stop some of them.

45:12.410 --> 45:15.046
How many is too many?

45:15.080 --> 45:18.984
You would deny them
the possibility of happiness?

45:19.017 --> 45:21.753
Of all there is here?

45:21.787 --> 45:24.489
You think that
this is happiness?

45:27.092 --> 45:29.795
I think it's as close
as some people can get.

45:31.362 --> 45:33.031
You included.

45:35.000 --> 45:36.734
And me.

45:40.939 --> 45:43.274
I love my son.

45:48.179 --> 45:50.448
You made
the wrong choice, Ed.

45:55.854 --> 45:58.023
LINDA [SIGHS]:
I wish I could have
saved you.

46:05.130 --> 46:07.065
[***]

46:18.143 --> 46:20.111
[TRAIN SIGNAL RINGING]

46:20.145 --> 46:22.247
[***]

46:37.929 --> 46:39.898
MAN:
I tried
to leave once.

46:41.332 --> 46:43.101
I couldn't
do it.

46:45.170 --> 46:47.072
I pity you.

46:48.139 --> 46:50.008
And I envy you.

46:52.110 --> 46:54.045
What's your story, then?

46:55.246 --> 46:57.182
What did this place fix?

46:58.249 --> 47:00.518
I did damage to children.

47:04.289 --> 47:06.491
Does that make you
want to hurt me?

47:07.959 --> 47:10.028
It makes me
want to hurt myself.

47:12.898 --> 47:15.166
